theorem closure_interior_closure_eq_closure_interior_of_P1
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hP1 : Topology.P1 A) :
    closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) = closure (interior A) := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  ·
    exact
      Topology.closure_interior_subset_closure_interior_closure (A := A)
  ·
    have hIntSub : interior (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure A :=
      interior_subset
    have hClos₁ :
        closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) ⊆ closure A :=
      closure_mono hIntSub
    have hClos₂ :
        closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) :=
      Topology.closure_subset_closure_interior_of_P1 (A := A) hP1
    exact Set.Subset.trans hClos₁ hClos₂

theorem closure_eq_closure_interior_closure_of_P1
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hP1 : Topology.P1 A) :
    closure A = closure (interior (closure A)) := by
  -- We establish the two inclusions separately.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  ·
    -- From `P1` we have `A ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
    have h₁ : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) := hP1
    -- Monotonicity of `interior` gives `interior A ⊆ interior (closure A)`,
    -- hence after taking closures we get the next inclusion.
    have h₂ : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
      apply closure_mono
      have : interior A ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
        apply interior_mono
        exact subset_closure
      exact this
    -- Combining the two inclusions and taking `closure` yields
    -- `closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))`.
    exact closure_mono (Set.Subset.trans h₁ h₂)
  ·
    -- The reverse inclusion follows directly from monotonicity of `closure`,
    -- applied to `interior_subset : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A`.
    have h : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
    have : closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure (closure A) :=
      closure_mono h
    simpa [closure_closure] using this

theorem interior_subset_interior_closure_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure (interior A)) := by
  -- First, note the basic inclusion `interior A ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
  have h :
      interior (interior A) ⊆ interior (closure (interior A)) := by
    apply interior_mono
    exact (subset_closure : (interior A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A))
  -- Rewrite `interior (interior A)` as `interior A` to obtain the goal.
  simpa [interior_interior] using h
